+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017ioPNyP6nQ16zX2gpwE4kq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No incomplete checkpoint. No existing source files. This is a greenfield project. Non-interactive environment detected — using Autopilot.\n\n**Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot.**\n\nStarting autopilot. I'll narrate each decision. Let me design this document management API.\n\n---\n\n**Q: How to structure the source files?**\n→ Choosing: Feature-based modules (users, folders, documents, permissions, activity) with a central app entry point\n  Reasoning: The task has 5 clear domains. Keeping them in separate modules makes code navigable and testable independently. A single `src/app.ts` exports `createApp()` as required.\n\n**Q: Authentication strategy?**\n→ Choosing: UUID tokens stored in an in-memory Map (token → userId)\n  Reasoning: Simple, no JWT library needed, stateless per-request lookup is O(1), matches \"Token-based auth\" requirement without overengineering.\n\n**Q: Permission resolution for multiple paths?**\n→ Choosing: Collect all roles from direct share + inherited folder shares, return highest precedence (owner > editor > viewer)\n  Reasoning: Spec says \"most permissive role\" when access comes via multiple paths. Simple role ranking.\n\n**Q: Activity log storage?**\n→ Choosing: Append-only array, filtered by user permissions on GET /activity\n  Reasoning: Simple, no pagination needed, timestamps for ordering.\n\nNow proceeding to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":326,"cache_read_input_tokens":22294,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":326},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe8a621f-9a0b-41c4-b673-7c874e955721","uuid":"0476f176-fa11-442c-890e-23c6e7aed50e"}
